Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.13,0:01:54.58,Default,Yumemaro,0,0,0,,{TIME:113130,114589}Kuma-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.58,0:01:55.79,Default,Yumemaro,0,0,0,,{TIME:114589,115799}Kuma-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.79,0:01:58.63,Default,Yumemaro,0,0,0,,{TIME:115799,118635}Kuma-san, come on!\NWait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.63,0:02:02.22,Default,Yumemaro,0,0,0,,{TIME:119636,122222}Kuma-san, please\Nthink it over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.22,0:02:03.80,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:122222,123807}Back off.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.89,0:02:08.64,Default,Yumemaro,0,0,0,,{TIME:124891,128645}Tatsu-san says you should get\Npermission from Nozomi first, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.64,0:02:10.43,Default,Yumemaro,0,0,0,,{TIME:128645,130439}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.43,0:02:13.19,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:130439,133191}But I'm doing it for her sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.19,0:02:14.90,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:133191,134901}Why do I need her permission?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.90,0:02:16.65,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:134901,136653}Keep your mouth shut.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.65,0:02:21.07,Default,Yumemaro,0,0,0,,{TIME:136653,141074}What are you going to say to Nozomi if you go\Nto Egawa-sensei and make things even worse?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.07,0:02:24.28,Default,Yumemaro,0,0,0,,{TIME:141074,144286}Tatsu-san told you,\Nshe can't be associated with yakuza.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.28,0:02:25.16,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:144286,145162}Shut the hell up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.16,0:02:30.00,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:145162,150000}I'm going there to work things out,\Nnot make them worse. What's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.00,0:02:32.16,Default,Yumemaro,0,0,0,,{TIME:150000,152169}Tatsu-san says you shouldn't go…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.16,0:02:34.17,Default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{TIME:152169,154171}– Ah!\N– Don't follow me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.88,0:02:43.68,Default,[title],0,0,0,,{TIME:155881,163680}{\fad(800,100)\t(6299,7799,3,\1c&H101010&\3c&H101010&\4c&H101010&)}— Episode 07 —\NThe Canary That's Forgotten How To Sing{NOTE:da\\N歌を忘れたカナリヤ}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.30,0:02:48.43,Sign,(sign),0,0,0,,{TIME:164306,168435}{\1c&H101010&\3c&H101010&\4c&H101010&\t(0,2000,\1c&HD3F0CB&\3c&H020400&\4c&H000000&)}Egawa Isao
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.81,0:02:57.94,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:173815,177944}Boy, I've never met anyone\Nwho lived in such place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.78,0:03:06.74,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:184785,186745}What the hell are you doing?\NWatch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.74,0:03:09.66,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:186745,189664}Uh… Do you have\Nan appointment with Egawa-sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.33,0:03:16.17,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:192334,196171}Ah, who would've thought\Nthat it'd rain today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.17,0:03:18.17,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:196171,198173}Huh? Ah, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.29,0:03:23.17,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:199299,203178}Tell Egawa-sensei that the poor bastard\NKumagorō is here to talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.17,0:03:27.68,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:203178,207682}Ah… sure thing.\NPlease wait here for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.06,0:03:32.22,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:210060,212229}Good thing I kept my cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.22,0:03:32.68,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:212229,212687}Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.40,0:03:41.53,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:220403,221530}Kumagorō?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.73,0:03:45.15,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:222739,225158}He was a bit strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.45,0:03:50.99,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:229454,230997}Hm? Hey, Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.99,0:03:53.91,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:230997,233917}It's me, it's me!\NThe Mine Nozomi guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.00,0:03:56.83,Default,Egawa Isao,0,0,0,,{TIME:235001,236837}Have him leave premises.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.83,0:04:01.92,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:236837,241925}Keh! Here I am yelling at the top of my lungs\Nand he doesn't even bother answering.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.55,0:04:05.51,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:243552,245512}Is this the bad time,\Nis he busy with work?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.51,0:04:07.76,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:245512,247764}Uh, I must ask you to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.76,0:04:08.51,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:247764,248515}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.51,0:04:10.80,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:248515,250809}You can't see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.80,0:04:12.47,Default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{TIME:250809,252477}– But why—\N– Leave at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.47,0:04:15.10,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:252477,255105}Listen to me, miss! I'm—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.10,0:04:17.52,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:255105,257524}I know, I know,\Nbut no means no.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.52,0:04:19.77,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:257524,259776}Please don't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.77,0:04:23.32,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:259776,263321}If I don't see him, I'll have the future\Nof a certain girl on my conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.32,0:04:25.69,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:263321,265699}When he says no,\Nit means no.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.69,0:04:27.99,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:265699,267993}Now leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.99,0:04:29.49,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:267993,269494}Alright, I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.49,0:04:31.74,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:269494,271746}If you're gonna be like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.74,0:04:34.20,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:271746,274207}be my guest.\NI won't budge from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.62,0:04:37.29,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:275625,277294}What a stubborn man.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.62,0:04:39.42,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:278628,279421}Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.42,0:04:42.42,Default,Kumagorō,0,0,0,,{TIME:279421,282424}You're such a cold fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.42,0:04:44.17,Default,Sune,0,0,0,,{TIME:282424,284175}Bye bye.
